DataElement.preferredName: Triglycerides Median Baseline Laboratory Result Value in mg/dL
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A laboratory result using the metric measure of milligrams per deciliter (mg/dL) to capture the median result for fats composed of three fatty acid chains linked to a glycerol molecule.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: The imaginary standard against which the measurement of fats composed of three fatty acid chains linked to a glycerol molecule is compared.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: Fats composed of three fatty acid chains linked to a glycerol molecule.
